    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 1: biochemical fractions of mouse forebrain show C9orf72 to be localized to both the pre- and post-synaptic compartment.\n\nFigure 2: IP+WB of PSD95 (DLG4) yields C9orf72 and Rab39b (Fig. 2a). Immunofluorescent imaging from C9-WT mossy fiber synapses demonstrated partial overlap of C9orf72 with pre-synaptic (Synpr), post-synaptic (PSD-95), and dendritic (MAP 2) proteins (Fig. 2c). C9orf72 was partially co-localized with Rab39b in the mossy fiber synapse region of C9-WT mice (Fig. 2c), indicating that C9orf72 shares synaptic localization with previously identified interactors.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Knockout C9orf72 mice were obtained through a generous gift from\"\n\nantibody:\nC9orf72, GeneTex, GTX634482, Ms monoclonal",
